The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of the graph isomorphism problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper focuses on the parallel and space complexity of the problem, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper studies the problem for specific graph classes, such as cographs and interval graphs, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper uses logspace algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
